77.1	Resolution_Trust_Corporation	Resolution Trust Corporation	The Resolution Trust Corporation was a United States Government-owned asset management company run by Lewis William Seidman and charged with liquidating assets, primarily real estate-related assets such as mortgage loans, that had been assets of savings and loan associations (S&amp;Ls) declared insolvent by the Office of Thrift Supervision (OTS) as a consequence of the savings and loan crisis of the 1980s. It also took over the insurance functions of the former Federal Home Loan Bank Board.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/RTC_literature_by_Matthew_Bisanz.JPG/200px-RTC_literature_by_Matthew_Bisanz.JPG
